006package gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.core.model.constraint;
007
008import gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.core.model.IAssemblyDefinition;
009import gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.core.model.ISource;
010import gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.core.model.constraint.impl.AbstractDefinitionTargetedConstraints;
011
012import edu.umd.cs.findbugs.annotations.NonNull;
013
014/**
015 * A set of constraints targeting a {@link IAssemblyDefinition} based on a
016 * target Metapath expression.
017 *
018 * @see #getTargetExpression()
019 */
020public class AssemblyTargetedConstraints
021    extends AbstractDefinitionTargetedConstraints<IAssemblyDefinition, IModelConstrained>
022    implements IFeatureModelConstrained {
023
024  /**
025   * Construct a new set of targeted constraints.
026   *
027   * @param source
028   *          information about the resource the constraints were sources from
029   * @param target
030   *          the Metapath expression that can be used to find matching targets
031   * @param constraints
032   *          the constraints to apply to matching targets
033   */
034  public AssemblyTargetedConstraints(
035      @NonNull ISource source,
036      @NonNull String target,
037      @NonNull IModelConstrained constraints) {
038    super(source, target, constraints);
039  }
040
041  @Override
042  public void target(@NonNull IAssemblyDefinition definition) {
043    applyTo(definition);
044  }
045
046  @Override
047  protected void applyTo(@NonNull IAssemblyDefinition definition) {
048    super.applyTo(definition);
049    getIndexConstraints().forEach(definition::addConstraint);
050    getUniqueConstraints().forEach(definition::addConstraint);
051    getHasCardinalityConstraints().forEach(definition::addConstraint);
052  }
053}
